#JerusalemaDanceChallenge Ndlovu style. Big love and respect to Master KG for bringing the world together. 🇿🇦❤️🙌🏾 #JerusalemaDanceChallenge JOHANNESBURG - The Ndlovu Youth Choir has accepted the Jerusalema dance challenge by performing a rendition of the popular hit song. The choir shared their own version of the song on social media on Monday. READ: Ramaphosa urges SA to do Jerusalema dance for Heritage Day  "#JerusalemaDanceChallenge￼ Ndlovu style. Big love and respect to @MasterKGsa for bringing the world together," read a post from the choir. Master KG's popular song has inspired a global dance craze and has more than 148-million views on YouTube.